vaasudEvayani (Daruvu)
raagam: kalyaaNi
65 mEcakalyaaNi mEla
Aa: S R2 G3 M2 P D2 N3 S
Av: S N3 D2 P M2 G3 R2 S

taaLam: aadi
Composer: Tyaagaraaja
Language: Telugu

pallavi

vAsudEvayani veDalina Itau vAriku nI ganarE

anupallavi

vAsavAdi sura pUjituDai vrija nayanauni madini dalcucunu

caraNam 1

nIrukavi dOvatulanu gaTTi niDala munanu shrI cUrNamu beTTi 
sAri veDali I saphalO juTTi sAreku bangAru kOlanu baTTi

caraNam 2

mATi mATikini mIsamu duvvi manmatha rUpuDu dAnani krovvi 
dATi dATi paDucunu tA nivvi dambuna balkucu pakapaka navvi

caraNam 3

bAgu mIra naTanamu sEyucunu patita pAvuni tA vEDucunu 
rAga tALa gatulanu pADucunu tyAgarAja sannutuni pogaDucunu

Other information:
Lyrics contributed by Lakshman Ragde.

This song is NOT a kriti, it is a Daruvu. It is the introductory lyric of Thyagaraja's Dance Drama "Prahlaada Bhakta Vijayam" and introduces the character "Douvaarikudu" who goes to visit Sri Krishna.

Song performed for karnATik by Bindu Nair.

